20:
OWWIE! Why can CATS land on their 
feet, but not foxes? That is hardly fair.
31:
Stella! We meet again! I find this most 
pleasing!
39: Well, I certainly am A real Inaho!
44:
I don't understand, though. 
Why are you here?
49:
Here? Excellent question. This IS 
awfully empty and dreary for a dream.
53:
Oh, I know! 
Come, Stella, I have thought of 
a much better place to dream in!
59:
Lovely! The scenery here should prove 
far more enjoyable. It has long been 
my favorite!
66:
Ahaha! The place of my dreams, 
indeed!
71:
I didn't know you can visit people's 
dreams, Inaho.
76:
Mwahaha! Impressive, is it not? 
A simple task for a yokai as powerful 
as myself!
79:
A-although I may have, ah, 
BORROWED a small trinket from my 
mother's collection.
85:
The Crystal of Connections. 
A treasure which enables its user to 
communicate with anyone their 
imagination fancies, apparently.
88:
Mother said I must never EVER touch 
it! Which naturally translates to: 
Inaho, you simply MUST play with this 
fancy little rock!
99: T-that is no longer of my concern!
102:
I have already made up my mind! 
I, Tamamo Inaho, shall run away from 
home!
111:
Be-because Mother is a big! Fat! 
Meanieee!
You shan't believe what she has done 
THIS time!
117:
I spoke with her about you and all the 
adventures we had. How we fought 
that dumb diviner, how I got to play 
with Soushiro...
119:
And she said she'll not tolerate her 
daughter playing with humans! 
...No matter what she says, I know 
you would never betray me!
122:
She grounded me for life—for LIFE!—
and sealed off our connection to the 
mortal realm.
125: How did you get here then?
128:
I connected my dream to yours, 
so I am here in spirit only.
130:
Oooh, I should have plotted my 
getaway FIRST!
I-I will be in—sniffle—in SO much 
trouble when Mother finds ouuuut!
143: YOU! Do not think I have forgotten!
147:
This day shall be your last! Behold the 
TRUE power of the Nine Tails!
150:
Oh? Nothing to say for yourself? After 
all the malice you spewed last time?!
156:
This is weird...
Perhaps, did you come to enjoy the 
scenery with us?
158:
I TOLD you sharing dreams is hardly 
so difficult as—
167: Hmph! What is HER problem? Still a meanie, I see!
173:
I'll help you run away from home. 
We can try using the World Flipper.
181:
Yes, as long as we are connected 
via dream.
183:
I think I can establish a link between 
your world and Starview Village.
186:
Oooh, Mother DEFINITELY will not be 
pleased...
189:
She can't ground you if she can't 
catch you.
193:
Ahaha! You have a little mischief in 
you after all!
200:
World Flipper activated. 
Commencing remote launch.
